@{b}@{i}<character>@{ui}, @{i}<commands-to-character>@{ui}@{ub} (V4)

@{h4}Special commands
          @{b}save@{ub}: Save the current game position to file.
       @{b}restore@{ub}: Restore a previously saved game position from file.
      @{b}ram save@{ub}: Save the current game position in RAM memory. (V3/V4)
   @{b}ram restore@{ub}: Restore the latest saved game position from RAM. (V3/V4)
     @{b}undo@{ub}/@{b}oops@{ub}: Restore the game position to before your last command. (V3/V4)
       @{b}restart@{ub}: Restart the game. (V3/V4)
          @{b}help@{ub}: Print help or hints.
 @{b}brief@{ub}/@{b}verbose@{ub}: Select location description mode. (V3/V4)
  @{b}exits on@{ub}/@{b}off@{ub}: Automatically report exits on or off. (V4)
@{b}words@{ub}/@{b}pictures@{ub}: Turn pictures on or off.
         @{b}score@{ub}: Print the current score.
     @{b}again@{ub} (@{b}a@{ub}): Repeat the last command.

@{h4}Interpreter commands
            @{b}#save@{ub}: Like @{b}save@{ub}, but bypasses any disk change prompts.
         @{b}#restore@{ub}: Like @{b}restore@{ub}, but bypasses any copy protection schemes.
            @{b}#quit@{ub}: Quit the game.
@{b}#picture @{i}<number>@{ui}@{ub}: Test command: show the picture with the given @{i}<number>@{ui}.
   @{b}#seed @{i}<number>@{ui}@{ub}: Test command: set the random number seed to a given @{i}<number>@{ui}.
            @{b}#play@{ub}: Test command: play back a script file as the game input.

