@{c}@{h3}JEWELS OF DARKNESS TRILOGY

@{" Colossal Adventure " LINK COLOSSAL_ADV}
@{" Adventure Quest " LINK ADVENT_QUEST}
@{" Dungeon Adventure " LINK DUNGEON_ADVENT}

             @{b}Year@{ub}: @{i}1986@{ui} (@{i}1982@{ui})
@{b}Original platform@{ub}: @{i}Atari ST@{ui}
     @{b}Game version@{ub}: @{i}V3@{ui}
    @{b}Graphics type@{ub}: @{i}Line-drawn@{ui}

The three games comprising the @{b}Jewels of Darkness@{ub} trilogy were Level 9's
earliest releases. Issued as three individual games in 1982 under Level 9's
own brand, they were originally known informally as the @{b}Middle Earth Trilogy@{ub}.
Later, the games were significantly revised and updated and published together
as a formal trilogy in lavish packaging by Rainbird in 1986, under the new
collective title, @{b}Jewels of Darkness@{ub}.

