@{c}@{h3}MULTIPLE CHOICE GAMES

@{" The Archers " LINK THE_ARCHERS}
@{" The Secret Diary of Adrian Mole " LINK ADRIAN_MOLE_1}
@{" The Growing Pains of Adrian Mole " LINK ADRIAN_MOLE_2}

             @{b}Year@{ub}: @{i}1985-7@{ui}
@{b}Original platform@{ub}: @{i}Amstrad CPC@{ui}
     @{b}Game version@{ub}: @{i}V3@{ui}
    @{b}Graphics type@{ub}: @{i}Line-drawn@{ui}

Level 9 published three multiple-choice games; they were not so much adventures
as interactive stories in which the player was presented with a series of
choices that could affect the progress of the game to a greater or lesser
extent. The first such game was @{b}The Archers@{ub} for Mosaic Publishing;
the second, also for Mosaic and published in the same year (1985), was an
adaptation of @{b}The Secret Diary of Adrian Mole@{ub}, the first instalment in
Sue Townsend's hugely popular series. The final game of this type was another
Adrian Mole book adaptation, this time based on the similarly popular @{b}Growing
Pains@{ub} sequel. This was not published by Mosaic, however, but rather by Virgin.

